Copy the gbp directory to /etc/puppet/modules
Copy the hieradata directory to where hiera is pointing to
Edir the defaults.yaml in hieradata with the correct values
cd puppet-template
./mudule.sh
puppet apply site.pp -v -d

Repeat above for all nodes

Once the puppet run on controller completes, add the switch config as shown below to the ml2_config_cisco_apic.ini.
Add "--config-file /etc/neutron/plugins/ml2/ml2_config_cisco_apic.ini" to the sysVinit,upstart,systemd file (as
recommended by the distro) and restart neutrn.

[apic_switch:101]
compute01 = 1/1

[apic_switch:103]
compute02 = 1/1
